<p>
	What are the benefits of massage treatment on your health and wellbeing? There are many, but these 5 key benefits certainly make it worthwhile!</p>
<h3>
	1. Alleviation of back pain</h3>
<p>
	Back pain is one of the most common reasons that people seek massage therapy, and it can be invaluable in helping to relieve lower back pain. Massage helps to improve the range of motion, while endorphins released during massage are natural painkillers. It can also help to improve posture, which in turn an help to reduce back pain.</p>
<h3>
	2. Easing muscular pain&nbsp;</h3>
<p>
	Massage can help to relax and soften tired or injured muscles, and exercise and strengthen muscles that may be weak, tight or atrophied. Massage can also aid recovery from sports injuries and reduce the prevalence of spasms and cramping. It also helps reduce pain and stiffness in patients suffering with arthritis.&nbsp;</p>
<h3>
	3. Improved circulation</h3>
<p>
	The heart is one of your most vital organs, and massage can help to keep it health by improving your circulation. This improved circulation also ensures that other organs are receiving plenty of nutrients and oxygen. Massage can also help to lower the blood pressure, keeping the heart and other organs healthy and reducing the risk of heart attack and stroke.</p>
<h3>
	4. Promoting good mental health</h3>
<p>
	It has long been accepted that having a massage can help to relieve stress, but now there is a definitive correlation between massage and reduced depression and anxiety. All those endorphins make you feel good, while massage therapy boosts energy levels, concentration levels, and enhances the quality of your sleep, all of which help us to maintain good mental health.</p>
<h3>
	5. Improved skin condition</h3>
<p>
	<span style="font-size: 12px;">The skin is the biggest organ in the body, and massage therapy can help to look after it. It promotes tissue regeneration, helping to reduce scar tissue and stretch marks. It has been shown to help the recovery of burns patients, reducing their pain and itching and therefore their anxiety levels.</span></p>
